A Star Point Pattern (45)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to Play.\b0
\par After black 1 and white 2 are played, we learned that it is the correct direction for black to cut on the left side with 3.
\par
\par When white connects at 4, black intends to seal off the upper side.
\par
\par What is the best sequence?
\par }
