Diagram 1 (Usually Powerful)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is usually a powerful move for black to push with 1 and begin to seal off white in order to create thickness towards the upper side.
\par
\par White resists by bending at 2 first. Blocking with black 3 is natural.
\par
\par And then -
\par }
