Diagram 2 (Neck and Neck)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White hanes at 1, nd when black cuts with 2, white plays dansu at 3, leaving black with a weak group to deal with. Then, after black defends with 4, white 5 captures the black stone on the lower side.
\par
\par Black defends his territory on the right with 6 without too much complaint.
\par
\par The result is neck and neck. It iss hard to tell who's better.
\par
\par \pard\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\qj Later, after white \b\f1 A\b0\f0  and black \b\f1 B\b0\f0  are played, there will the a large fight. The game will be complicated from now on.
\par \pard\ltrpar
\par }
